It emerged yesterday that a Maths paper, which was written on Monday, had been leaked in the Mopani district. JOHANNESBURG - The Basic Education Department says it is trying to establish how many pupils have been affected by a matric exam paper leak in Limpopo.It emerged yesterday that a Maths paper, which was written on Monday, had been leaked in the Mopani district.The department's Elijah Mhlanga says mobile phones were used to distribute copies of the paper. What we are doing now is to establish the extent. Last year, we thought it was three learners and we ended up with something like 16 schools, so you need to allow for the investigation to happen. There was an exam paper leak in Limpopo last year as well.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)